## .NET Performance Analysis — `CaseTransformExtensions.cs`

### Scan Execution Checklist
| Recipe | Hits |
|--------|------|
| `.ToLower()`/`.ToUpper()` | 2 |
| `RegexOptions.Compiled` | 7 (3 guarded by `#else`, 3 static unconditional, 1 per-instance) |
| `[GeneratedRegex]` | 3 |
| `new Regex(` in non-static context | 1 (per-instance in `InflectionRule`) |
| `.Substring(` | 2 (same line) |
| `sealed class` | 0 of 1 non-static class |

---

### Findings

#### 1. Triple Regex Replace Chain + `.ToLower()` in `Underscore()` 🟡 Moderate (1 instance)
**Impact:** 4 intermediate string allocations per call. At millions of calls this is massive GC pressure.  
**File:** CaseTransformExtensions.cs:L115-121  
**Fix:** Replace with a single-pass `StringBuilder` or `string.Create()` that walks the input once, inserting `_` at boundaries and lowercasing in place:
```csharp
public static string Underscore(this string input)
{
    if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(input)) return input;
    var sb = new StringBuilder(input.Length + 4);
    for (int i = 0; i < input.Length; i++)
    {
        char c = input[i];
        if (c == '-' || c == ' ') { sb.Append('_'); continue; }
        if (i > 0 && char.IsUpper(c))
        {
            char prev = input[i - 1];
            if (char.IsLower(prev) || char.IsDigit(prev))
                sb.Append('_');
            else if (i + 1 < input.Length && char.IsLower(input[i + 1]) && char.IsUpper(prev))
                sb.Append('_');
        }
        sb.Append(char.ToLowerInvariant(c));
    }
    return sb.ToString();
}
